<br>
Back in my earlier days I was fighting gnolls on the south side of the split paw spires.  I got into trouble and cast yonder.  I ended up a good bit north of the spires and had plenty of time to cast gate.<br>
<br>
That gets me thinking.  I can cover a lot of ground with Yonder very quickly, what if Yonder just always sent you in the direction you were facing as opposed to some random direction?  I could get across South Karan in like 10 casts of Yonder in about 30 seconds.<br>
<br>
Ideas on how this would be implemented:  Use the exact same algorithm as Yonder, just fix the direction (the direction you are facing) and distance it would go.  This could be done by either adding a new line of spells or maybe add another spell like Iceflame of Ec'i that applies to  Yonder.  So you first cast the buff to make Yonder predictable and then point your nose in the direction you want and cast Yonder.  This spell would probably need to be disallowed in zones that do not allow Levitate, but I would make it castable indoors.<br>
<br>
I do not think this would make Wizards too powerful or make SoW undesireable.  You could not do this while invis because you'd have to cast several times.  There would be some risk to it because you may know what direction you are facing, but you may not even be able to see your destination due to trees/clip plane/etc.  You could not use it for Corpse Recovery because you'd get teleported too far from a corpse.<br>
<br>
I must admit this I am envious of those that can cast SoW, and I see this as a fun way for Wizards to be able to get around more quickly, while still retaining their wizardly identity.<br>
<br>
Thoughts?  Suggestions?  Could this be abused?  Would it change class balance?   I just think it would be a lot of fun to hop around a zone and give me a reason to use a spell that does not spend much time in a gem slot these days. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 3:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: instead of SoW...</span><hr size=1> Good thinking,<br>
